<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="952" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d952">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367116/93.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 116.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 173, of the 16th
                            ultimo, concerning the status of the negotiations respecting American
                            educational and <pb facs="0972" n="860" xml:id="pg_860"/> missionary
                            institutions in the Ottoman Empire, has been received and read with
                            attention.</p>
                        <p>The difficulties with which you are meeting in your efforts to press the
                            negotiations to a successful conclusion are fully understood, and your
                            action in the matter has the approval of the department.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington
                            Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>